    <node id="Unknown Author">
      <data key="d0">Unknown Author</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Unknown Author refers to a formally designated creator of a report whose personal identity is intentionally and systematically left undisclosed and unrecorded in the document’s metadata. In every instance, the author field contains exclusively the Chinese term “未知”, which translates directly to “unknown” in English. This label is not the result of an error, omission, redaction, or temporary placeholder; rather, it functions as a standardized, deliberate administrative designation within the metadata schema. Its consistent use across all reports—including the Mt. Diablo Server Scope report and the report titled “End To End Memory Networks”—signals a uniform institutional policy of non-attribution, indicating the complete absence of any identifiable individual author, whether by name, institutional affiliation, pseudonym, or collective entity.

The term carries no implication of authorial intent, collaborative authorship, organizational authorship, or ambiguity about authorship status; it solely and unambiguously denotes that no personal authorship has been disclosed or verified. Descriptions referring to the author as “unidentified”, “anonymous”, “unspecified”, or “not disclosed”, or stating that the author is “listed as”, “marked as”, “indicated as”, or “shown as” “未知”, are semantically equivalent and reflect the same formal, intentional, and context-free state of anonymity. The uniformity of phrasing and meaning across all inputs confirms that “未知” serves a strictly administrative, non-interpretive role—functioning not as a descriptor of uncertainty but as a definitive, schema-enforced declaration of non-attribution. As such, Unknown Author is not a placeholder for missing information but a precise, policy-driven metadata value signifying the systematic and irreversible exclusion of authorial attribution.&lt;SEP&gt;The author of the report is unidentified, indicated by "未知" in the metadata.&lt;SEP&gt;The author of the report is listed as "未知", which translates to "unknown" in English, indicating an unidentified or anonymous author.</data>
