    <node id="PDF Format">
      <data key="d0">PDF Format</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">PDF Format refers to the Portable Document Format, a standardized digital document file type widely used for report distribution and archival storage. It is designed to preserve document structure, typography, layout, and security features across diverse platforms and devices, ensuring consistent rendering regardless of the software or hardware environment. Multiple descriptions confirm that the report—specifically identified in one instance as the “Mt. Diablo Server Scope report”—is consistently distributed and stored in PDF Format, underscoring its role as the official, canonical file representation. This functional consistency supports reliable dissemination, maintains document fidelity, and enables systematic recordkeeping within institutional workflows.

The descriptions collectively document at least thirteen distinct instances of the report saved as separate PDF files, with recorded file sizes of 0.58 MB, 0.60 MB, 0.75 MB, 0.91 MB, 0.98 MB, 1.03 MB, 1.43 MB, 1.44 MB, 1.72 MB, 1.80 MB, 1.92 MB, 1.99 MB, 2.28 MB, 2.63 MB, 2.72 MB, 3.48 MB, 4.32 MB, and 5.05 MB. These variations indicate multiple versions or iterations—potentially differing in content, metadata, embedded resources (e.g., images, fonts, or annotations), compression settings, or generation tools. At least three archival timestamps are explicitly recorded: 2026-03-07 at 19:05:19, 19:05:21, and 19:05:23—all referencing 入库 (ingestion or archival) events and likely corresponding to different versions. One additional description notes an unspecified 入库 timestamp, further supporting the interpretation of multiple archival actions over time. One description also specifies local storage at a defined file path, highlighting operational diversity in how these PDF instances are managed across systems. Collectively, the evidence affirms that PDF Format serves not only as a technical standard for cross-platform fidelity but also as a procedural anchor in institutional documentation practices.&lt;SEP&gt;PDF Format refers to the file format of the report, which is ".pdf".</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5642f5d2398a5cb6600146cb1001b0ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3993cd0b737e3130edf76f25d51050ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1547ad065c68b2f6fec2e3b6eb6a9099&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fda2d54a8413eca19fea985df0ff580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c984e299ac9432c7e312cc7b398b600&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22d5697b8505125995b91427be92e6d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04159a2e6b1c0a304c8cab9dc130201f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0b6845c9f5c77a0f3f30fa98403d8fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e24b7488a587cd1f8bf6573d12f1c75a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f1a30530b2b434213d044c2a8466044&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c8929bd6af5efae83044622ffa3faac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1c174d3bf65d5024ebe4ad7cbd8c5e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e88d373c00da121b8868d08bdceb9cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32749bfe06ebb4fd503585308b574af7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ae046aa80e7382953f272a3870f099b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71812bc0fbded857fe0a4b82f5223b84&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0559e293569f15eabf0cd28fac35d14f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c461db61ef0a922e7d7292d8516c1147&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11fbfb718c91a1cacf50d05e7bcc41bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7480ef95765b1d3cb3e7cc5a73e67e91&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87108b0686e8d70e6c11c7ad5b493573&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01a392db9d8bb576ab6ed5aff9f9d578&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41e5bcd0e2dad86fc34ddddd1afe3ac0</data>
