    <node id="Core Priority">
      <data key="d0">Core Priority</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Core Priority is a classification tag used within a research library system and organizational classification framework to denote a report's high strategic importance. It functions as a formal priority level assigned to documents, signifying that the report holds exceptional relevance for organizational knowledge management, research objectives, and strategic decision-making. This classification distinguishes critical resources from those of standard or lower priority within the library's knowledge infrastructure. While its broader operational context encompasses the entire research library or collection, supporting information retrieval and curation, it is specifically applied to individual reports to signal their elevated significance within the repository.

The Core Priority designation is embedded in the report's metadata rather than existing as a standalone document or process. It appears in multiple linguistic and syntactic forms, including the English label "priority: core", the bilingual Chinese-English designation "优先级/核心", and standalone references to "core" as a priority descriptor. All variants consistently convey the same evaluative meaning across contexts. Although the tag is notably applied to reports in the server architecture domain, descriptions uniformly affirm its role as an indicator of high importance or critical status. Minor variations in wording regarding the library environment reflect contextual nuance rather than definitional divergence, collectively underscoring its institutional function as a key element of the classification framework.&lt;SEP&gt;The priority level assigned to the document indicating core importance.&lt;SEP&gt;The priority level assigned to the report, marked as core.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3993cd0b737e3130edf76f25d51050ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17e8fab522b31c893a3a7ef21633d42a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49a4b3d9e081e0db5971a564684cb895&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-147c4db7a4ce5872858a38c1ac58af56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0b6845c9f5c77a0f3f30fa98403d8fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d829808f9b4093bb903d5990d12a27c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df115efbf3bc71602047949ae3dbbdf0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15484e8b32164d9fb60eeef755439770&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f1a30530b2b434213d044c2a8466044&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c8929bd6af5efae83044622ffa3faac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99116bb42021db2c45f55b65671842c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71812bc0fbded857fe0a4b82f5223b84&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97525ceaf715f1ad94448c8abc5642db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f023cd84d3e2ed9cf707d62efd5ddbb9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fed70deae9eaf1b4120dec7d0e6498bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-266b57d952795e78de135dd7ea0d1822&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41e5bcd0e2dad86fc34ddddd1afe3ac0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d28fc57f74bd152b123d626835823bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60ca18023b7448fb4ddf9aa784ef1a65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7fd39ddee62a6682cc2d3e58c3b66ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bef51647317cfab8fd98c2182da0b1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3b581e41172762e088bcf3b7f03c6a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7fcd9c795c3ffe5951ea1b509567b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec101ba502a70816a33b6a1e26f6054f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1773341508</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Research Report Library">
      <data key="d0">Research Report Library</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Research Report Library is a curated, structured knowledge management system designed to function as a centralized repository for storing and organizing technical reports. Operating as a digital collection, it ensures documents are systematically classified rather than passively aggregated. This system emphasizes deliberate selection and organization, serving as a logical category or tag group under which documents are classified. It supports domain-specific technical knowledge management, ensuring that reports are stored and categorized within a defined library or collection system.

Organization within the Research Report Library is achieved through hierarchical tagging and file path navigation, which serve as metadata identifiers signaling a document's placement within the library's taxonomy. The entity functions as the collection category indicated by these document tags and file paths, acting as a category tag indicating the document belongs to a research report collection. Classification schemes include domain and priority levels, such as Core and Server Architecture. Specific tags derived from the system, such as the Chinese-language tag 研报库/核心 (Research Report Library/Core) and its expanded variant【核心】服务器架构 (Core Server Architecture), indicate both the broader collection and the precise subcategory. These tags assign the document to a core research report collection, confirming the library's role as the library category where the report is stored.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3993cd0b737e3130edf76f25d51050ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3556e182081aed4b9613c75949ed570&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ae046aa80e7382953f272a3870f099b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c199ec006c1f0210255474d03892899b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97525ceaf715f1ad94448c8abc5642db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0559e293569f15eabf0cd28fac35d14f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-900ad8221a96dafc212eef7868a063e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bf489aadb0f21630c59b8361f23e8f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41e5bcd0e2dad86fc34ddddd1afe3ac0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7bc46115f13aecdbbcd6e7398ee9691&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33d6bc980e862376c11685a00bf22ca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e27f03ec1e126815641b4755ece051c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bef51647317cfab8fd98c2182da0b1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-968fbcf059982c556b4bcc6944efa36b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3b581e41172762e088bcf3b7f03c6a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-635a8270f90d4ad369e34ef96c6f284f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-230764380b33557b5524bd06ee945029&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62991649d9ddbddbdd87eed4b8473959&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7fcd9c795c3ffe5951ea1b509567b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec101ba502a70816a33b6a1e26f6054f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df273047e67bbcef8888ccc637f02f26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caffd63ee8599ae7be43759f1b96b861</data>
