    <node id="Liufang">
      <data key="d0">Liufang</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Liufang is an entity defined exclusively through a technical, file-system-based association with specific technical reports, commonly the 7525 Report or HarDNet report. Lacking biographical or professional attributes, Liufang is identified solely through a local file path embedded within these documents, typically via a hyperlink labeled 原文链接 (original link). The path structure, file:///Users/liufang/Documents/Library/, anchors Liufang to a macOS device's local file system. This indicates the reports reside within Liufang's personal user directory, marking Liufang as a user name found in the document file path.

Liufang's role is strictly functional, delineated by a custodial relationship to the file's storage location. Characterized as ownership, curation, custody, or access rights, these formulations converge on Liufang controlling or maintaining the local instantiation of the report. Liufang is the user account owner associated with the file path where the document is stored. A concrete instance confirms Liufang as the owner of the path /Users/liufang/Documents/Library/【核心】服务器架构/[2025]_20250807%20CXLT%20302%201%20Pan%20copy.pdf. This establishes Liufang as the user owner of the digital storage location where the file is saved.

The emphasis on the local file URL underscores that Liufang's identity is metadata-driven and context-dependent. There is no evidence of multiple distinct individuals; variations reflect synonymous phrasings of the same functional role. Liufang functions as a de facto custodial anchor, embodying the report's local presence rather than an independent person. Liufang remains the user associated with the directory path where the report is stored on the local system, consistent with being the user identified in the document storage path.&lt;SEP&gt;Liufang is the user associated with the local file path where the document is stored.</data>
