    <node id="CXL">
      <data key="d0">CXL</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Compute Express Link (CXL) is an open interconnect standard enabling high-speed, low-latency communication between processors, memory, and accelerators in datacenters.&lt;SEP&gt;CXL (Compute Express Link) is an open interconnect standard enabling memory sharing and pooling across CPUs, GPUs, and accelerators, central to the report’s proposed memory solution.&lt;SEP&gt;Compute Express Link (CXL) is an open interconnect standard enabling high-speed, low-latency communication between processors, memory, and accelerators in datacenter environments.&lt;SEP&gt;An organization associated with the IDE specification.&lt;SEP&gt;Compute Express Link technology used as a basis for composable memory solutions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-17e8fab522b31c893a3a7ef21633d42a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef5a1dc3d7c28f0190c5185e1c92732b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f023cd84d3e2ed9cf707d62efd5ddbb9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bef51647317cfab8fd98c2182da0b1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caffd63ee8599ae7be43759f1b96b861</data>
