    <node id="Datacenter Memory Fabric">
      <data key="d0">Datacenter Memory Fabric</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A datacenter memory fabric refers to a scalable, shared memory infrastructure across servers and devices, enabled by technologies like CXL.&lt;SEP&gt;A datacenter memory fabric refers to a scalable, composable memory infrastructure that allows pooling and sharing of memory resources across servers using technologies like CXL.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-17e8fab522b31c893a3a7ef21633d42a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f023cd84d3e2ed9cf707d62efd5ddbb9</data>
