    <node id="Report">
      <data key="d0">Report</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Report is a formal, structured document type used to present technical analysis, findings, specifications, and performance data—primarily within the domain of next-generation server architectures. It serves as a high-fidelity vehicle for research dissemination, conveying analytical depth, empirical data, architectural proposals, and actionable recommendations. As a document type, “Report” is explicitly encoded in metadata under the ‘type’ field and consistently associated with core priority, archival in the server architecture research library, and standardized documentation conventions. Its functional purpose spans multiple specialized technical contexts, including CXL-enabled memory management in datacenters, security considerations in PCIe 6 switch deployments, AI interconnects, memory fabric design, and OCP-aligned infrastructure enhancements—evidenced by distinct titles such as *“DC Memory Fabric management: An In Depth Review of the K8s OCP Reference Implementation”* and *“PCIe 7.0 Enhancements for high speed I/O connectivity for OCP server Infrastructure.”*

The Report is predominantly distributed in PDF format (.pdf), though one description identifies a Markdown (.md) variant—indicating format flexibility while preserving structural rigor and core-priority classification. Metadata consistently includes title, author, date, format, priority, and subject-domain tags, with all instances categorized under “server architecture research” and designated as core-priority items in both ingestion and archival systems. Archival occurs in a vectorized research library, with ingestion timestamps recorded as 2026-03-07 at 19:05:20 (7.37 MB file size) and 2026-03-08 (23.88 MB file size); these discrepancies reflect version-specific finalization or ingestion events rather than contradictory publication dates. The March 2026 date appears across multiple entries and is best interpreted as the authoritative versioning timeframe for this cohort of reports. Collectively, these Reports constitute authoritative, metadata-rich artifacts designed for internal evaluation, cross-team technical alignment, and long-term reference in evolving hardware, interconnect, and system design domains.&lt;SEP&gt;The report is a structured document in PDF format, dated 2026-03-07, tagged under core server architecture, and vectorized for retrieval.&lt;SEP&gt;The report is a technical document titled "Composable Memory Fabric Architecture Enabling Scalable Memory Management for AI and General Purpose Compute", formatted as a PDF with priority designation "core".&lt;SEP&gt;The type of document identified in the metadata.&lt;SEP&gt;The document type is classified as a report.&lt;SEP&gt;Report is the document type specified in the metadata.&lt;SEP&gt;The type classification of the document indicating it is a report.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-17e8fab522b31c893a3a7ef21633d42a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-954e8ea4f501064d07fa47f0e5affaeb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cb819bd8f7ecd3c6e4efa0548627c2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fda2d54a8413eca19fea985df0ff580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bea655fda74f25913c082a3a09d1a75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-147c4db7a4ce5872858a38c1ac58af56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecc05e1389a9315c30e68199bddd8d73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df115efbf3bc71602047949ae3dbbdf0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15484e8b32164d9fb60eeef755439770&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-207b0823e90b60e301db1f919be31b9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4173aa4ed70cd6d625ee79aebe2a677&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7dd14306d9061dddba8b150d9c7d98b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c461db61ef0a922e7d7292d8516c1147&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03978f9015d72cc2c030ac8e6447fed7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-538e9be43efc9f4740b1699a18d33882&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f023cd84d3e2ed9cf707d62efd5ddbb9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fad482b7206fdfbdc48ed9c3de6c7af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b71eacebd07cf22c28bd1377859a2954&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55f9a5f9dbd8556e5eeb84b9bb117c15&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01a392db9d8bb576ab6ed5aff9f9d578&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc91c144f09ce8648b8a92d03b6a031&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57adc984bf533daad96d70c0a73d33e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fde36569763e8e63f5879815d072c123&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7fd39ddee62a6682cc2d3e58c3b66ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33d6bc980e862376c11685a00bf22ca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-968fbcf059982c556b4bcc6944efa36b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-230764380b33557b5524bd06ee945029&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de484dab9dc735b91436af3e79491149</data>
