    <node id="Open Compute Project">
      <data key="d0">Open Compute Project</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The Open Compute Project is an open-source hardware initiative that develops scalable, efficient data center hardware standards, including memory system architectures.&lt;SEP&gt;An open-source hardware initiative developing standards for scalable, efficient, and secure data center infrastructure.&lt;SEP&gt;The Open Compute Project is an industry consortium driving open-source hardware designs for data center infrastructure, including servers and networking equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;The Open Compute Project is a collaborative community focused on designing and enabling efficient, scalable, and open hardware for data centers.&lt;SEP&gt;The Open Compute Project is an organization that develops open-source hardware designs for data center and server infrastructure.&lt;SEP&gt;The Open Compute Project is a collaborative community focused on designing and sharing efficient, scalable, and open hardware specifications for data center infrastructure, including compute servers.&lt;SEP&gt;The Open Compute Project is a collaborative community developing open-source hardware designs for data center infrastructure, including servers, storage, and networking.</data>
